I had 6 chicken thighs I needed to use up, and this was a great way to do it! And I didn't mind that they were bone-in, either, it just makes my husband eat slower... Two unnecessary steps in this recipe as I see it: don't replace the olive oil after you've browned the chicken. Why toss out all that flavor if you're only going to add more oil back into the pan? The flour that remains also makes the last step redundant; when you remove the chicken for serving, you don't need to bring it all to boil again for reduction, it's already nicely thickened and ready to go (just skim off the fat). We served it alongside buttered noodles and a nice glass of red... oh, but I do agree with a previous writer in that I will rememeber to put a shake of chili flakes in next time to give it a kick. And fyi, I used the bagged Marinara sauce that you find in the refridgerated pasta section, plus the leftovers from a bad bottle of wine, not Marsala.

