Great cacciatore recipe, and I've tried a few. Nice to have thicker cuts of mushrooms, and I like recipes that include Marsala and capers. I dipped the chicken in egg before coating it with flour (thank you Lidia Bastianich!). For the marinara sauce I used a quick recipe from Marcella Hazan's "Essentials of Classic Italian Cooking": 2 cups of Italian plum tomatoes with their juice, 5 tbls butter, 1 medium onion cut in half, salt. Add all ingredients in small pot and cook at slow temp for 45 minutes; at end of cooking discard onion. I really think this fresh sauce added a lot to the recipe -- it added to the overall fresh and delicious taste of the recipe. In sum, this recipe is a keeper.

